From 5f31a8e75051d444a03ae043267466b349b3dd4f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 14:22:43 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 Batch 5: markdown HTML support + avatars on
 Discussion
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Flip `supportHtml: true` on PR description and comment body markdown
  rendering. The renderer's default sanitizer allowlist already covers
  every tag PLAN.md called out (`<details>` / `<summary>` / `<kbd>` /
  `<sub>` / `<sup>` / `<br>`), so collapsed-spoiler blocks in PR
  descriptions and HTML emphasis in comments now render rather than
  getting stripped.
- Comment headers in the Discussion timeline grow a 20px circular
  avatar to the left of the author name. Image source is GitHub's
  `avatarUrl` with `?s=40` appended (idempotent), and a deterministic
  initial-letter chip — coloured by a hash of the login — fills in
  when no `avatarUrl` is on the user record.
---
